Integument
. Body brown, covered by microgranular cerotegument (diameter of granules less than 
1
). Surface of anterior and lateral parts of prodorsum, lamellae, subcapitular mentum and genital plates with small foveolae (diameter up to 
6
). Centrodorsal surface of prodorsum smooth. Surface of notogaster tuberculate; tubercles (diameter up to 
8
) forming a polygonal ornamentation. Surface of ventral side, femora and trochanters III, IV with large foveolae (diameter up to 
16
), forming a reticulate ornamentation.

